**Product 2 Image**
====================
### Overview

The following code is used to display the product 2 image on a webpage. The image is stored in the `images` directory and is named `product2.jpg`.

### Frontend Code (HTML, CSS, JS)
#### HTML
```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Product 2 Image</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="product-image-container">
        <img src="images/product2.jpg" alt="Product 2 Image" id="product2-image">
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

#### CSS
```css
/* styles.css */
.product-image-container {
    width: 50%;
    margin: 40px auto;
    text-align: center;
}

#product2-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}
```

#### JavaScript
```javascript
// script.js
const product2Image = document.getElementById('product2-image');

// Add event listener to image
product2Image.addEventListener('click', () => {
    // Perform action when image is clicked
    console.log('Product 2 image clicked');
});
```

### Backend Code (Core PHP)
#### PHP
```php
// product2.php
<?php
// Check if image exists
if (file_exists('images/product2.jpg')) {
    // Display image
    $image = 'images/product2.jpg';
    header('Content-Type: image/jpeg');
    readfile($image);
} else {
    // Display error message
    echo 'Image not found';
}
```

### Database Code (MySQL / MariaDB)
#### SQL
```sql
-- create table
CREATE TABLE products (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    name VARCHAR(255),
    image_url VARCHAR(255)
);

-- insert data
INSERT INTO products (name, image_url) VALUES ('Product 2', 'images/product2.jpg');

-- retrieve data
SELECT * FROM products WHERE name = 'Product 2';
```

### Full Logic
1. The user requests the webpage by navigating to `index.html`.
2. The browser loads the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files.
3. The JavaScript code adds an event listener to the product 2 image.
4. When the image is clicked, the JavaScript code logs a message to the console.
5. The PHP code checks if the image exists and displays it if it does.
6. The SQL code creates a table to store product information, inserts data into the table, and retrieves data from the table.

### Example Use Case
To use this code, simply create a new directory and add the following files:
* `index.html`
* `styles.css`
* `script.js`
* `product2.php`
* `images/product2.jpg`

Then, navigate to `index.html` in your browser to view the product 2 image. Clicking on the image will log a message to the console.

Note: This code assumes that the image is stored in the `images` directory and is named `product2.jpg`. You may need to adjust the file paths and names to match your specific use case.